--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
README : EXPRESS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

eXpress is a streaming DNA/RNA sequence quantification tool, primarily developed for application to RNA-Seq transcript-level abundance estimation.

More details, installation instructions, and the manual can be found at http://bio.math.berkeley.edu/eXpress.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
I.   Authors:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Adam Roberts designed and wrote eXpress, with substantial technical input 
from Lior Pachter. 

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
II.  Requirements:
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

eXpress is a standalone tool that requires gcc 4.0 or greater, and runs on Linux and OS X.   It depends on Boost (http://www.boost.org) and BamTools (https://github.com/pezmaster31/bamtools).

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
III. Learn More (Installation, Manual, etc.):
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Installation steps, tutorial, manual, documentation, etc. are all available 
through the eXpress website:
http://bio.math.berkeley.edu/eXpress

Join the mailing list to stay informed of updates and announcements:
http://groups.google.com/group/express-announcements

